Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.03,0:00:04.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Has there been any contact with\NCount Mazuurek since then?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.62,0:00:08.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. However, his Landing Castle \Nis still functional.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.20,0:00:13.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If its Aldnoah is still active, that\Nmeans that Count Mazuurek is alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.71,0:00:17.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps he is lying low and\Nwaiting for an opening. Or perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.71,0:00:19.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Or perhaps he has been taken\Nprisoner by the Terrans.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.88,0:00:24.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, it would be prudent to assume \Nthat Count Mazuurek will not return.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.59,0:00:27.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, there is but\None course of action.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.60,0:00:30.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What are you...?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.02,0:00:36.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot allow that Earthborn\Nstray to run loose any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.84,0:02:26.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Resupplying and inspection operations\Nare on schedule. No delays reported.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.51,0:02:27.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As for Kataphrakt repairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.97,0:02:31.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we are working in concert with the\Nbase's repair depot to get back on schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.51,0:02:34.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very good. Carry on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.47,0:02:35.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.85,0:02:37.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And our Mars Knight guest?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.27,0:02:40.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not a word. He appears\Nto be the silent type.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.73,0:02:45.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusaki, do you know why men who are\Nthe silent type are so attractive?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.03,0:02:48.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because they always\Nseem calm and collected?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.11,0:02:51.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's because they sit quietly and\Nlisten to what you have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.41,0:02:52.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And our replacement crew?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.78,0:02:58.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, ma'am. They're already aboard,\Nand station shifts have been revised.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.33,0:03:00.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A few of them were members\Nof our previous crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.71,0:03:03.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Warrant Officer Kaizuka and Lt. Marito.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.50,0:03:08.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As well as Dr. Yagarai, who is now serving as an\Nofficial medical officer with the rank of ensign.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.51,0:03:13.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, there has been a request from\NEnsign Kaizuka to interrogate the Mars Knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.39,0:03:15.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From Kaizuka Junior?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.06,0:03:17.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He says he wants to use\Nhis analytical engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.23,0:03:23.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You programmed this yourself, Inaho?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.86,0:03:26.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All I did was customize the firmware\Nthat it was already running.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.65,0:03:34.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The area it's tied into has\Nbeen expanded, too. How's it feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.12,0:03:35.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not all that different.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.04,0:03:39.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Try not to expand it\Nany further, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.75,0:03:42.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By the time you notice it's affecting \Nyour brain, it'll already be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.54,0:03:44.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't. I'm aware of the risks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.26,0:03:49.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.84,0:03:52.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.47,0:03:53.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Got a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.43,0:03:58.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nao, why did you decide to\Nserve aboard this ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.98,0:03:59.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.23,0:04:04.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no reason\Nfor you to fight, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.36,0:04:07.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should have packed up and left\Nonce your injuries were healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.48,0:04:09.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same for you, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.35,0:04:12.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not. I'm a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.11,0:04:16.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There was no reason for you to become\Na soldier, so it is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.87,0:04:18.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is not!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.62,0:04:26.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I regret it every day...\NThat I made you into a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.34,0:04:31.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I saw you that day,\N unconscious and covered in blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.55,0:04:34.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I asked myself,\N"Why didn't I stop you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.22,0:04:42.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I became a soldier because I wanted to\Nprotect you and the world you live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.10,0:04:45.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you still...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.98,0:04:50.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. But I can't stand\Naround doing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.36,0:04:54.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's because of the princess, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.87,0:05:00.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That girl's not the Princess\NAsseylum you used to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.75,0:05:03.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's now an enemy who's trying\Nto conquer the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.12,0:05:06.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That person is a fake. The real one\Nis still alive somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.71,0:05:08.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How could you\Npossibly know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.59,0:05:10.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's what my left eye determined.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.17,0:05:16.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from the situation, I think\Nshe's being held against her will.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.01,0:05:20.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I want to rescue Seylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.27,0:05:21.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.98,0:05:25.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki, she was shot right in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.98,0:05:31.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was hurt, and she was shot\Nas she was trying to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.07,0:05:36.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I have to save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.20,0:05:38.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nao...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.71,0:05:49.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.30,0:05:52.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is the Kataphrakt's status?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.59,0:05:55.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When they ran diagnostics,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.22,0:05:58.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,they found even the sub-frame had \Nbeen warped by the gravity waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.72,0:06:01.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it basically \Nneeds an overhaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.35,0:06:03.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you quit drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.23,0:06:07.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My primary physician is a real nag.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.44,0:06:10.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess a toast is out\Nof the question, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.36,0:06:12.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's always room for toasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.07,0:06:14.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.99,0:06:18.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was doctor's orders. Medicinal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.95,0:06:23.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.83,0:06:30.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not very well, looks like. I heard you \Nwere subjected to a full body search.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.92,0:06:35.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I never imagined I would be subjected\Nto such primitive questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.51,0:06:39.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't have you using\Na poison tooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.84,0:06:41.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What an outdated notion...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.51,0:06:43.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That does seem to be\Nyour national character.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.22,0:06:47.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From a Terran's point of view,\NI suppose Vers' feudal system
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.98,0:06:49.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,would seem just as anachronistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.40,0:06:53.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it's a problem,\Nchange it yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.78,0:06:56.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Spoken like someone born\Ninto a land of plenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.82,0:06:58.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're like pigs who\Nare about to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.28,0:07:02.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once you are too cold\Nto move, it is too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.49,0:07:03.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You know quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.32,0:07:05.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You admit I'm right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.66,0:07:10.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, about pigs. Even though Princess\NAsseylum had never seen birds before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.25,0:07:13.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have spoken to\NPrincess Asseylum?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.00,0:07:15.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She spent time aboard this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.17,0:07:21.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You are one of those who\Nsought to exploit her, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.80,0:07:24.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't exploitation.\NIt was cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.64,0:07:25.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Cooperation, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.47,0:07:28.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell me one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.81,0:07:34.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do I look like a man who would\Nsell out his country lightly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.86,0:07:37.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't look that way.\NOr sound that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.28,0:07:39.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which makes you the\Nperfect man to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.70,0:07:47.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you sworn loyalty\Nto Princess Asseylum?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.01,0:08:00.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to eat, Rayet?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.05,0:08:03.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't eat a little, you won't have\Nany energy when we go into battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.26,0:08:05.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.76,0:08:08.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With fasting diets, the weight starts\Ncoming off at your boobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.43,0:08:11.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've never gone on\Na diet before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.15,0:08:15.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You've never dieted before, Rayet?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.78,0:08:21.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing! How do you\Nkeep that figure?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.18,0:08:23.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would you tell me, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.70,0:08:25.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.91,0:08:27.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Having lunch, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.99,0:08:31.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it would be nice to eat somewhere\Nbesides the ship while we're in port.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.61,0:08:34.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, we don't get to eat out\Nvery often, do we?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.92,0:08:38.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me,\Nhas anyone seen Inaho?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.80,0:08:41.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to ask him to join us\Nfor lunch, but I haven't seen him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.59,0:08:46.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ensign Kaizuka is interrogating\Nthe Mars Knight at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.60,0:08:48.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho's interrogating him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.68,0:08:50.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm heading back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.14,0:08:53.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait... Rayet?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.94,0:08:58.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't tell us the\Nsecret to her figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.90,0:09:06.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, you are saying that the Princess Asseylum\Ncurrently at our moon base is an impostor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.03,0:09:07.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.41,0:09:12.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that is true, where is the real one?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.91,0:09:15.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is she being held prisoner somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.00,0:09:18.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or is there a reason she\Ncannot show herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.88,0:09:20.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Possibly both.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.59,0:09:22.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That left eye of yours\Nsaw through that, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.91,0:09:24.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's an analytical engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.02,0:09:37.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible! I am not so foolish that I\Nwould believe such a preposterous tale!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.65,0:09:40.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We've retrieved your Kataphrakt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.53,0:09:45.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Its Aldnoah Drive was knocked offline\Nby the force of the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.95,0:09:47.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It will never work again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.16,0:09:52.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You powered it down yourself, didn't you?\NOut of fear that Terrans would steal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.83,0:09:55.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't you listening? It stopped\Nworking after the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.21,0:10:00.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did it, now? Just as I thought,\Nyou shut it down intentionally.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.38,0:10:04.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will say it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.47,0:10:07.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum is an impostor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.14,0:10:12.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There are many species of birds, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.27,0:10:16.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Large birds. Small birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.48,0:10:19.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And brilliantly-colored birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.82,0:10:24.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.94,0:10:28.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is how birds\Nfly through Earth's skies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.87,0:10:34.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Most birds fly, but there are some\Nspecies of flightless birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.08,0:10:36.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Flightless birds?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.79,0:10:41.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suspect that Princess Asseylum\Nmight say that she finds it sad
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.21,0:10:44.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that they cannot fly\Neven though they have wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.34,0:10:48.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She is a kindhearted person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.26,0:10:51.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But their inability to fly does not\Ntrouble them in the least.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.93,0:10:55.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On the contrary, perhaps the ones \Nto be pitied are the birds
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.31,0:10:56.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,who can fly, but are kept in a cage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.69,0:10:59.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why would someone\Nlock them in a cage?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.52,0:11:06.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because they are so very beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.37,0:11:15.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum was shot\Nright in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.20,0:11:18.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shot by Count Saazbaum.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.58,0:11:19.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Preposterous!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.00,0:11:22.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who then left with Slaine Troyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.79,0:11:25.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They took Princess Asseylum, \Nwho was on the verge of death, with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.34,0:11:31.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saazbaum was celebrated as the\Nhero who rescued Princess Asseylum!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.39,0:11:33.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's no hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.81,0:11:37.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's the mastermind behind\Nthe plot to assassinate her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.18,0:11:39.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saazbaum is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.10,0:11:44.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those bastards tricked my father and\Nused him as much as they could
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.52,0:11:46.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then they killed him \Nlike some lowly insect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.61,0:11:48.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are Vers-born?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.16,0:11:51.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.61,0:11:55.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In any event, your father would\Nhave died sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.70,0:11:59.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Consider it a blessing that he wasn't\Nbranded a traitor and lynched.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.29,0:12:01.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.71,0:12:06.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying my father\Ndeserved to be killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.50,0:12:07.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.96,0:12:09.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not done with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.54,0:12:11.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.05,0:12:14.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.35,0:12:20.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You must think I'm an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.56,0:12:27.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That I'll always be bound by the past.\NAlways be a prisoner to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.69,0:12:30.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.\NI'm just like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.82,0:12:37.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All I can do is blame others.\NHate them, envy them, and fight them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.50,0:12:39.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A stupid Martian!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.46,0:12:42.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're different.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.09,0:12:42.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.21,0:12:44.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.11,0:12:44.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am not!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.29,0:12:46.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.04,0:12:49.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm no different!\NI hate Martians!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.92,0:12:54.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I hate myself\Nmost of all!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.52,0:13:02.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Marylcian, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.27,0:13:03.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.14,0:13:08.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He has been calling repeatedly, insisting that\Nhe be put through to Princess Asseylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.98,0:13:10.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What does Milord Slaine say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.90,0:13:13.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no sign of him, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.53,0:13:15.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is all this commotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.20,0:13:20.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.06,0:13:20.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.21,0:13:26.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear. You can't have your discussion\Nwith me in the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.58,0:13:27.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately not, Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.42,0:13:33.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Knowledge of your existence is limited,\Neven here at the moon base.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.17,0:13:35.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I must ask that you\Navoid public areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.39,0:13:36.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I speak to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.56,0:13:41.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's Count Marylcian, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.35,0:13:42.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But, Highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.78,0:13:44.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.48,0:13:50.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Patch him through\Nto the throne room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.70,0:13:57.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Her Highness Asseylum\Nis most gracious.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.12,0:14:00.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please forgive this\Nsudden disturbance.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:03.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is a pleasure to see you,\NCount Marylcian.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.58,0:14:07.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what did you wish\Nto discuss with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.21,0:14:09.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It must be urgent indeed\Nfor you to contact me
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.71,0:14:11.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,without first obtaining\NCount Troyard's permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.38,0:14:18.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ah. One cannot speak\Nto you in private?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.72,0:14:24.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I must say, Count Troyard is being rather\Noverprotective to keep you under guard thus.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.94,0:14:28.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps "under guard"\Nwas a poor choice of words.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.86,0:14:33.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He is more a knight who seeks to protect \Nhis princess imprisoned in her ivory tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.15,0:14:37.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my apologies if I\Nhave given offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.03,0:14:39.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I compared Your Highness\Nto a bird in a cage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.12,0:14:41.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A bird in a cage?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.87,0:14:44.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, that is the\Nexpression used on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.75,0:14:46.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to describe one who has been\Ndeprived of her freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.50,0:14:50.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Message from base command!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.04,0:14:52.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They report that the\Nprisoner has escaped!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.88,0:14:55.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Put the ship on alert!\NInform all duty stations!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.84,0:14:56.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.27,0:15:15.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These late-night alarms\Nare killing me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.61,0:15:20.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rayet, we have to get out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.41,0:15:23.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rayet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.96,0:15:28.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.08,0:15:29.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.93,0:15:39.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.14,0:15:48.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.31,0:15:52.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to go back\Nto your Landing Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.11,0:15:55.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and find out where the real\NPrincess Asseylum is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.11,0:15:57.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.19,0:16:01.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because you want the same thing\Nas Princess Asseylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.53,0:16:08.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that you ever had\Nany desire to attack Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.54,0:16:10.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your left eye also told you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.25,0:16:13.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell that much even\Nwithout using my left eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.04,0:16:16.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were very familiar with Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.26,0:16:21.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your interest in Earth goes beyond\Nits value as an invasion target.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.14,0:16:24.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you do see everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.89,0:16:27.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's one other thing that I\Nwant you to find out for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.31,0:16:32.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What Slaine Troyard's objective is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.56,0:16:37.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Keep going north and you'll reach\Nthe Martian Landing Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.82,0:16:39.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll need to walk from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.40,0:16:42.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.78,0:16:45.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Food and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.45,0:16:49.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't have you dying of thirst\Nbefore you get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.25,0:16:52.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't mind at all\Nif you did, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.17,0:16:57.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it comes down to it, I need you\Nto keep Princess Asseylum safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.67,0:17:03.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Before I go, may I\Nask you one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.89,0:17:06.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.26,0:17:13.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am Mazuurek, member of the\NVers Empire Orbital Knights' 37 Clans.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.10,0:17:18.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mazuurek... There's a type of folk\Nmusic on Earth with a similar name.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.86,0:17:24.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. As I researched my name's meaning,\NI became fascinated with Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.57,0:17:28.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.37,0:17:32.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho. Inaho Kaizuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.21,0:17:39.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Mazuurek. Take good care\Nof Princess Asseylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.96,0:17:44.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall do so, Inaho Kaizuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.35,0:17:52.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, why did you ask me\Nto help with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.52,0:17:53.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.06,0:17:57.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you think that I would\Nkill that Martian?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.98,0:18:00.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just like that time\Nwith Princess Asseylum?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.19,0:18:03.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, you didn't actually\Nkill her back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.70,0:18:05.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I failed to kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.20,0:18:05.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:06.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.99,0:18:07.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.60,0:18:09.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Give it a rest, I am not–
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.33,0:18:10.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.45,0:18:15.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're not the same person\Nyou were then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.42,0:18:22.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mustang Leader to Mustang 11.\NWhat's your status?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.51,0:18:24.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mustang 11, nothing to report.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.72,0:18:26.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Stay on alert.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.14,0:18:27.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.60,0:18:33.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Inaho...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.89,0:18:35.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.61,0:18:45.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.15,0:18:49.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who gave those Landing Castles\Nauthorization to dock?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.62,0:18:51.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord, it was—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.49,0:18:52.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.08,0:18:54.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.50,0:19:00.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Marylcian requested a personal\Naudience with Princess Asseylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.79,0:19:02.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so, I gave them\Npermission to dock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.63,0:19:09.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As Princess Asseylum.\NRather, a princess of Vers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.97,0:19:11.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you do such a thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.68,0:19:15.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's be off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.18,0:19:19.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It would be poor manners to\Nkeep our visitors waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.18,0:19:54.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are both humbled and delighted
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.31,0:19:59.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that Your Highness has granted\Nus an audience on such short notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.39,0:20:03.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Marylcian,\NCount Barouhcruz,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.31,0:20:07.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am most grateful to you both for\Nbolstering our orbital defenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.78,0:20:09.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Under normal circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.99,0:20:12.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I expect that you would wish to go\Ndown to Earth and expand your domains.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.12,0:20:17.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We shall leave the conquest of Earth in\Nthe hands of our like-minded brethren.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.33,0:20:19.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness needn't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.62,0:20:21.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That is good to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:25.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is a matter of\Neven greater import to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.05,0:20:32.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With the previous Count Saazbaum dead,\Nwho will succeed to the post of Royal Guard,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.39,0:20:34.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,who is charged with safeguarding\Nthe moon base and Your Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.10,0:20:40.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no cause for concern. \NI have taken over those duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.85,0:20:47.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum, I have come\Nto beg you to consider
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.90,0:20:51.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,giving me the honor of\Nserving at your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.61,0:20:54.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Count Marylcian, I have–
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.01,0:20:59.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will thank you to keep your\Ncomments to yourself, Terran!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.04,0:21:04.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is a fortress that flies\Nthe flag of the Vers Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.88,0:21:07.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that post were bestowed upon\Nthe previous Count Saazbaum,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.42,0:21:10.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,a man of great merit who\Nrescued Her Highness,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.30,0:21:12.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would be disappointed,\Nbut would nonetheless approve.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.76,0:21:17.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yet you, an Earthborn even if you are \Nhis adopted son, dare to think
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.46,0:21:20.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you can inherit that post \Nusing this turmoil as a pretext?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.14,0:21:24.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To have one of low blood set foot \Ninside the castle where a member
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.27,0:21:29.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of the venerable Vers imperial family \Ndwells is a fact that cannot be tolerated!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.26,0:21:34.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One who does not possess a Landing Castle\Nis unfit to call himself count.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.87,0:21:42.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are not qualified to protect\Nthis place, not in the least!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.79,0:21:45.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you suggesting, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.71,0:21:49.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That we determine which is more fit\Nto protect Her Highness,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.05,0:21:55.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,my Herschel or your Tharsis.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.76,0:22:00.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Troyard, I hereby\Nchallenge you to a duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.96,0:22:09.96,T1,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dawn of Intrigue
